This paper deals with wireless energy transfer (WET) system, which is a subfield of wireless communication. The paper focuses on optimizing the training design for a multiple-input single-output (MISO) WET system, which involves channel state information (CSI) and energy beamforming. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their limits. 

The paper also involves the use of multiple antennas and channel reciprocity, which are common topics in the arXiv CS sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

Furthermore, the paper proposes to maximize the net energy harvested at the energy receiver (ER), which involves optimization techniques and algorithms. This makes the paper relevant to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing and optimization of multimedia data. 

Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for learning the channel state information (CSI), which makes it relevant to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
